<br>
Agility: Physical agility; affects your probabolity of being hit in combat, how much damage you take per hit, and how fast you can learn some skills.<br>
<br>
Charisma: How various factions react to you; affects prices for merchants. Also affects spell effects for Enchanters and bards, and helps Bards sucessfully play more notes.<br>
<br>
Dexterity: Coordination' affects how much damage you deliver with a bow/thrown weapon, time between attacks, how fast you learnc ertain skills, and how often certain spells and weapons hit their mark. Also affects some skills and Bard songs.<br>
<br>
Wisdom: Affects how fast you learn specific skills. For a Ranger, Paladin, Shaman or Druid, it also affects maximum mana at each level.<br>
<br>
Intellegence: Same as Wisdom only with INt casters in it (i'm lazy)<br>
<br>
Stamina: HEalth and constitution; affects your maxmum number of hit points at each level.<br>
<br>
Strength: Physical Strength;affects how much you can carry, how much melee damage you deliver to a target, and how fast you learn some skills.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
As for AC, since AGi directly ties in with AC, I assume AC also affects how much you get hit and for how much...besides that it makes sense. PLate BP, more AC, less damage to the person wearing it.<br>
<br>
No logs, just what is printed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zebanar01>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 4:37:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8649.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yeah..</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I've read over the booklet answers for it before. However, Verant changes their answers so often its not even funny. For awhile they kept it under wraps, saying pretty much what you said. Then, they said that stats really only have major effects on how fast you learn skills. This sent Shamans into an uproar(around Kunark release) and now I really don't know what verant's stance is anymore. <br>
